                <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratori</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Caes</abbr><ex>ari</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucio</ex></expan> S<supplied reason="lost">eptimio</supplied> <lb n="2"/>Severo <expan><abbr>Pert<supplied reason="lost">in</supplied>ac</abbr><ex>i</ex></expan> A<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>ug</abbr><ex>usto</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="3"/>conservat<supplied reason="lost">ori</supplied> orb<supplied reason="lost">is</supplied> <lb n="4"/>Helveti pu<supplied reason="lost">bli</supplied>c<supplied reason="lost">e</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Mehrere, zum Teil aneinanderpassende Fragmente. (B); Cart 1915: Z. 3/4: conservat[ori] op(erum) p[ub(licorum)] / [C(oloniae)] Helveti(orum) IIvi[ri Col(onia)]; AE 1916: Z. 4: [p]u[bli]c[e].</p>
            </div>
